## Intro

Azure Cache for Redis is a fully managed service that provides a secure and dedicated Redis cache, managed by Microsoft.
Redis is an open-source, in-memory data structure store, used as a database, cache and message broker.
Premium SKU Redis Cache instances can be upgraded in-place to a high availability (HA) configuration to provide enhanced reliability and uptime for applications that rely on Redis.
Basic and Standard SKU Redis Cache instances can be upgraded to HA, but this requires re-creating the resource via terraform.
The redis cache instance must be in a supported Azure region in order to enable HA (UK South is a supported region).

## Enabling HA (Premium SKU only)

1. Navigate to the Redis Cache instance in the Azure portal.
2. In the left-hand menu, select "Advanced Settings".
3. Under "Zone Redundancy", tick the "Allocate zones automatically" checkbox.
4. Click "Save" to apply the changes.

The resource may then require a terraform import to bring the change back into terraform state.
See the [Terraform Import guide](../Terraform/terraform-import.html) for how this can be accomplished in code.

