## Enabling HA (Standard or Basic SKU)

A Standard or Basic SKU Redis Cache instance cannot be upgraded in-place to a High Availability configuration.
In order to enable HA on an existing Standard or Basic SKU Redis Cache instance, the Redis Cache instance must be re-created via terraform.
Alternatively, the instance can be upgraded in-place to a Premium SKU and then the HA enabled with the above method.
Redis Cache instances cannot be downgraded from Premium to Standard or Basic SKUs without re-creating.

To enable HA on a Standard or Basic SKU Redis Cache instance via terraform:

1. In the terraform code, manually specify the `available_zones` argument in the `cnp-module-tedis-cache` module block.
2. Run `terraform plan` to see the changes that will be applied. This will show that the existing Redis Cache instance will be destroyed and a new one created.
3. Run `terraform apply` to apply the changes. This will create a new Redis Cache instance with the specified availability zones.

Valid availability zones in UK South are 1, 2 and 3.  At least two zones must be specified to enable HA.